5.9 Create a New Catalog Item
Lesson
Service Catalog items are the foundation of self-service in ServiceNow, enabling users to request products, services, and resources through an intuitive interface. Creating well-designed catalog items improves user experience, standardizes request processes, and automates fulfillment workflows.

The Catalog Builder provides a guided, step-by-step interface for creating catalog items without requiring technical expertise. It walks you through essential configurations including basic information, visual design, categorization, questions (variables), and fulfillment automation—all in a user-friendly workflow.

