The company is launching a new corporate device program featuring the Infinity Holographic Handheld Device (HHD)—an innovative device that projects immersive holographic environments without requiring VR glasses. 

The IT Asset Management team has approved two configurations: 256GB and 512GB models, available in Crimson or Silver colors. As the newly designated Catalog Administrator, Bud Richman needs to create a Service Catalog item that allows employees to request the Infinity HHD through self-service. 

The catalog item must collect essential information including the employee's manager (for approval), desired memory configuration, and color preference.

Your task is to build this catalog item using the Catalog Builder, ensuring it appears in the Hardware category with clear questions, visual branding, and proper fulfillment configuration. 

This will enable employees to easily request the device while providing the Asset Management team with all necessary information for provisioning.

Task Objectives

This task requires you to impersonate another user. You must end the impersonation before selecting Show hint or Validate task.

1. Impersonate Bud Richman to perform catalog administration tasks.

2. Launch Catalog Builder and create a new catalog item.

3. Select the Standard items in Service Catalog template to begin.
Configure Basic Info:
- Item Name: Infinity HHD
- Short description: VR, but without the glasses
- Upload image: Infinity HHD.png
- Description: The Infinity Holographic Handheld Device (HHD) is capable of projecting immersive environments around you. What are you waiting for? Get the Infinity HHD!

4. Set Location: Configure the item to appear only in the Hardware category.

5. Create first question (variable):
- Question Type: Choice (Dropdown with fixed values)
- Question label: How much memory do you want in your Infinity HHD?
