5.9.9 Activate the flow
Lesson
Workflow Studio provides several menu options for managing your flows:

- Test: Test the flow to ensure it runs as expected before production use.

- Debug: Set breakpoints to step through execution and review configuration and runtime values.

- Activate/Deactivate: Control flow execution—activate to start running, deactivate to stop without deleting.

- Save: Save your changes to preserve your work.
More actions: Access additional options including Properties, Executions, and Flow Stages.

Important Note on Flow Changes
If you modify a flow after activating it, you must deactivate and then re-activate the flow for changes to take effect.

